programme.desc: In this touching coming-of-age tale, an 11-year-old boy is forced to grow up fast as he tries to help his ex-con uncle open a crab shack and go straight, only to find the business venture threatened by the uncle's violent past.

programme.title: Hitman
programme.desc: A genetically engineered assassin known as Agent 47 finds himself on the run with a hooker after he is double-crossed on a mission in Russia. Timothy Olyphant and Dougray Scott star in the explosive unrated adaptation of the popular video game. Olga Kurylenko, Robert Knepper, Ulrich Thomsen. Directed by Xavier Gens.

programme.title: John Q
programme.desc: Riveting thriller about a family man whose son needs a lifesaving heart-transplant operation. When his health-care plan doesn't cover the boy's medical procedure, he takes drastic steps to rectify the situation.

programme.title: The Score
programme.desc: Marlon Brando, Robert De Niro and Edward Norton team up in this tense caper about the daring heist of a priceless artifact of European royalty, but bickering among the principals threatens to precipitate a coup before the theft gets under way. Frank Oz directed. Angela Bassett, Gary Farmer, Jamie Harrold, Paul Soles.

programme.title: Anna
programme.desc: A strikingly beautiful woman unleashes her strength and skills in order to become one of the best government assassins in the world. Later, she is recruited by the CIA to kill KGB's head in exchanged for immediate retirement and lifetime protection.

programme.title: Red Dawn
programme.desc: A band of Colorado high-school students conduct guerrilla warfare against Soviet invaders during World War III.

programme.title: The Lovely Bones
programme.desc: This heart-wrenching drama centers on young teenager Susie Salmon, who is murdered by her neighbor and watches over her grieving parents from a heaven of her own creation. Susie must come to terms with her own death, while sharing the pain her father and mother are working through.

programme.title: The Shack
programme.desc: After enduring a terrible tragedy, a father receives a mysterious invitation to visit a nearby shack. There, he experiences a divine intervention from a group of strangers, who lead him on a theological inquiry in this uplifting faith-based drama.

programme.title: Abandon
programme.desc: A bright college student is haunted by her past in this atmospheric thriller. Katie Burke is a driven senior at a prestigious college whose boyfriend, Embry, vanished years earlier. Katie's life unravels when a cop investigates the disappearance and Embry begins showing up on campus.

programme.title: The Judge
programme.desc: A big time lawyer returns home to defend his father, a local judge, against a murder charge in this poignant family drama. As the trial commences, the urbane counselor slowly begins to reconnect with his roots.

programme.title: Hall Pass
programme.desc: Pals Rick (Owen Wilson) and Fred are granted permission to take a week off of marriage, only to realize that the reality of single life is less appealing after bumbling in their efforts to become lotharios in this delightfully naughty marriage comedy. Later, when their wives decide to follow suit, things really get interesting.

programme.title: Before Sunrise
programme.desc: A young American travelling through Europe meets a French student on a train. Over the course of one 24-hour period, they explore the city of Vienna, walking and talking into the wee hours of the night and slowly falling in love.

programme.title: Crash
programme.desc: Sandra Bullock, Don Cheadle and Matt Dillon head a superb cast in this tense and insightful ensemble drama about a dozen Los Angeles residents and their experiences with various forms of racism. Jennifer Esposito, Brendan Fraser, Terrence Howard, Chris Bridges.

programme.title: Planet of the Apes
programme.desc: Director Tim Burton reimagines the 1968 sci-fi classic in this visually stunning feature set in 2029. Mark Wahlberg stars as an astronaut who crash-lands on a planet where dignified apes rule with an iron fist and subservient humans are treated like chattel. Helena Bonham Carter, Tim Roth, Michael Clarke Duncan, Paul Giamatti, Kris Kristofferson, David Warner, Estella Warren.

programme.title: Can You Keep A Secret?
programme.desc: Emma reveals her deepest secrets to the stranger sitting on the plane beside her, believing that the plane will inevitably crash due to the intense turbulence. Much to her dismay, she discovers that her seatmate is the CEO of the company she will be working with over the course of her business trip, and he knows every detail of her most embarrassing stories.

programme.title: New Year's Eve
programme.desc: Featuring an all-star cast including Robert De Niro, Katherine Heigl and Sarah Jessica Parker, this engaging comedy-drama follows a variety of couples and singles as they roam the streets of New York City on New Year's Eve.

programme.title: The Manhattan Project
programme.desc: A whiz kid constructs a thermonuclear device with the help of his girlfriend after stealing a cache of plutonium from the doctor who is romantically involved with his mother.

programme.title: Alita: Battle Angel
programme.desc: A cyborg with no memories and mastery of a lost and powerful cyborg martial art awakens in a post-apocalyptic dystopia caused by a global technological catastrophe. With the help of the scientist who revived her, she confronts her many enemies in a battle for justice within a fallen world.

programme.title: Fear
programme.desc: What begins as an innocent teenage romance turns to obsession when a charismatic but unbalanced young man sets his sights on a 16-year-old girl.

programme.title: Missing in Action 2: The Beginning
programme.desc: A soldier in Vietnam is taken prisoner and forced to grow opium under the control of a sadistic Colonel who forces the men to sign false confessions. He organizes an escape with his fellow POWs.

programme.title: Shanghai Surprise
programme.desc: During the Japanese occupation of China, a prim missionary hires a con man to help her locate a stolen cache of opium to use on wounded soldiers.

programme.title: Company Business
programme.desc: A former CIA agent is tasked with accompanying a captured KGB mole to Berlin for a spy swap. The two uncover an international conspiracy and are chased around Europe by both their agencies.

programme.title: American Son
programme.desc: A marine, fresh out of boot camp, returns home for Thanksgiving before being sent to Iraq. He faces family strife, while dealing with a budding relationship and animosity from jealous friends.

programme.title: House
programme.desc: In this chilling and suspenseful psychological thriller, two couples seek refuge from a madman in what they think is a deserted house in the woods, but they're right where he wants them. Allana Bale, J.P. Davis, Heidi Dippold.

programme.title: Brown Sugar
programme.desc: The world of hip-hop music serves as a dynamic backdrop to this engaging romantic comedy about a rap-music record producer (Taye Diggs) and a music journalist (Sanaa Lathan) whose long-time friendship blossoms into romance. Mos Def, Queen Latifah, Nicole Ari Parker, Wendell Pierce, Boris Kodjoe, Erik Weiner, Reggi Wyns.

programme.title: Hackers
programme.desc: High-school students stumble onto an embezzlement scheme and use computer wizardry to thwart the mastermind.

programme.title: Vice
programme.desc: Prepare for serious thrills as a cop pursues a female android that escaped from a hedonistic resort where people live out their wildest fantasies. Meanwhile, the owner of the resort dispatches a band of mercenaries to eliminate the android first.

programme.title: Envy
programme.desc: Here's a true Black comedy. That's because it stars Jack Black. He's a blast as a suddenly successful entrepreneur whose best friend and neighbor (Ben Stiller) resents his buddy's good fortune and rues the fact that he blew the opportunity to join him in his wildly lucrative venture. Christopher Walken excels as a barroom philosopher who imparts some dubious advice to Stiller. Barry Levinson directed. Rachel Weisz, Amy Poehler.

programme.title: Good Boys
programme.desc: One day, 12-year-old Max gets invited by the cool kids to a kissing party. Panicked because he doesn't know how to kiss, he enlists the help of two of his friends, Thor and Lucas, to help him uncover the mystery of kissing. After online research proves to be unproductive, they decide to take the drone owned by Max's father in order to spy on the neighboring teens. When the drone unexpectedly crashes, the boys are thrust into an adventure.

programme.title: Long Shot
programme.desc: A talented journalist unexpectedly bumps into his former babysitter who is now running for the presidency. Feeling a deep connection, she hires him to be her speechwriter and a romantic relationship develops between the two, despite being totally unprepared for her high profile lifestyle.

programme.title: Six Days, Seven Nights
programme.desc: In this romantic comedy, Anne Heche plays an ambitious magazine editor who becomes marooned on a deserted island with a gruff cargo pilot (Harrison Ford). Despite their conflicting personalities, the two castaways gradually fall for one another, even as they are besieged by mother nature and ruthless modern-day pirates. David Schwimmer, Jacqueline Obradors, Temuerra Morrison, Allison Janney.

programme.title: Crimson Peak
programme.desc: In this terrifying gothic romance, a mysterious stranger woos a young woman and brings her to his mansion atop a clay mountain. There, she learns that her new home holds many disturbing secrets as she fights for her sanity and her very life.

programme.title: Black Rain
programme.desc: A tarnished New York cop and his younger partner run afoul of the Japanese Yakuza after escorting a crime boss to Osaka in order to stand trial.

programme.title: Hitchcock
programme.desc: This exquisite biographical drama explores the relationship between Alfred Hitchcock and his wife Alma during the production of the classic 1960 film "Psycho.".

programme.title: Her Smell
programme.desc: A fading '90s punk rocker struggles with life after the past success of her all-female grunge band. Now playing smaller venues and competing against her own sobriety and the pressures of motherhood, she takes a hiatus from the stage, to find herself and her sober creativity.

programme.title: John Q
programme.desc: Riveting thriller about a family man whose son needs a lifesaving heart-transplant operation. When his health-care plan doesn't cover the boy's medical procedure, he takes drastic steps to rectify the situation.

programme.title: Surrogates
programme.desc: This dazzling, futuristic sci-fi thriller follows Greer, an FBI agent investigating a murder in a world where people no longer go outside but instead live life through robotic surrogates controlled from their homes. As Greer amasses clues, he uncovers a conspiracy involving the people responsible for creating the surrogates.

programme.title: Half Nelson
programme.desc: This poignant and moving two-character study is set in a poor Brooklyn neighborhood where a junior-high student (Shareeka Epps) catches her dedicated and inspiring teacher (Ryan Gosling) getting high. Surprisingly, the two begin a tentative friendship that could lead to each other's salvation. Newcomer Epps earns an A-plus for an impressively restrained performance, and Gosling is also excellent. Directed by Ryan Fleck, who co-wrote the script with Anna Boden. Anthony Mackie.
